01:32.994 --> 01:37.396
Sync and corrected by dr.jackson
for www.addic7ed.com

02:17.292 --> 02:18.892
♪

02:20.995 --> 02:23.097
Uh, lord Megatron,

02:23.099 --> 02:26.166
far be it from me to question
your intentions,

02:26.168 --> 02:27.768
but I do not understand

02:27.770 --> 02:30.838
why we've returned here
after all this time...

02:30.840 --> 02:32.840
alone.

02:32.842 --> 02:34.241
Uh...

02:36.277 --> 02:40.247
Every last trace of Energon
was extracted from this mine.

02:40.249 --> 02:43.550
There's nothing left.

02:44.686 --> 02:47.855
Indulge me, Starscream,
won't you?

02:58.399 --> 03:01.802
Miko! Mi...

03:01.804 --> 03:03.070
Check it out!

03:03.072 --> 03:05.906
Now, this would make
an awesome rehearsal space!

03:07.442 --> 03:08.809
[ Echoing ] Hello!

03:08.811 --> 03:11.512
Hello, Cleveland!

03:12.981 --> 03:16.049
Are you ready to rock?

03:16.051 --> 03:19.353
Whoo-hoo-ow!

03:19.355 --> 03:20.621
Arcee...

03:20.623 --> 03:21.955
Found something.

03:21.957 --> 03:23.857
Bulkhead?

03:23.859 --> 03:25.859
Bulkhead, do you read?

03:25.861 --> 03:28.529
[ Static ] Scrap.

03:28.531 --> 03:31.965
The mineral composition down
here is causing interference.

03:31.967 --> 03:35.002
Okay, maybe the acoustics
<i>aren't</i> perfect.

03:35.004 --> 03:36.770
[ Sighs ] Well, we're here.

03:36.772 --> 03:39.239
Ratchet's gonna want a sample.

03:39.241 --> 03:41.441
[ Device beeping ]

03:58.059 --> 04:00.260
How intriguing.

04:00.262 --> 04:02.663
[ Chuckles nervously ]

04:02.665 --> 04:03.830
[ Groans ]

04:03.832 --> 04:07.000
Incompetent fools!

04:07.002 --> 04:10.070
This mining equipment
should have been relocated.

04:10.072 --> 04:11.838
Why is it still here?

04:11.840 --> 04:13.707
A most valid question.

04:13.709 --> 04:14.741
[ Inhales sharply ]

04:14.743 --> 04:16.510
My apologies, master.

04:16.512 --> 04:19.379
I believe sound wave
was in charge

04:19.380 --> 04:21.481
of coordinating transport.

04:21.483 --> 04:23.550
[ Growls ]

04:23.552 --> 04:24.751
But in fairness,

04:24.753 --> 04:27.054
during your
interstellar travels,

04:27.056 --> 04:30.257
we all had to assume
additional responsibilities.

04:30.259 --> 04:32.593
Clearly, mistakes were made.

04:32.595 --> 04:35.095
Yes.

04:35.097 --> 04:36.496
Clearly.

04:39.601 --> 04:41.101
[ Gasping ]

04:42.403 --> 04:46.173
Every last trace
of Energon extracted?

04:46.175 --> 04:49.042
Lord Megatron, I can explain.

04:49.044 --> 04:50.277
Explain what?

04:50.279 --> 04:52.646
That you've been hoarding
a supply of Energon

04:52.648 --> 04:54.047
for your personal use?

04:54.049 --> 04:58.385
No! Not exactly.
You see, I...

04:58.387 --> 05:01.421
Do not take me for a fool,
Starscream!

05:01.423 --> 05:03.056
[ Stammers ]

05:03.058 --> 05:06.493
I have been wise
to your transgressions

05:06.495 --> 05:07.961
from the beginning.

05:07.963 --> 05:11.732
Not only did you pluck
the dark Energon from my chest

05:11.734 --> 05:14.601
in a failed attempt
to snuff my spark,

05:14.603 --> 05:18.505
but you tried to raise
your own undead warrior with it.

05:18.507 --> 05:22.142
It's no secret that you lost
an arm in the process,

05:22.144 --> 05:24.645
which you've
since had replaced.

05:24.647 --> 05:28.248
You know about that?!

05:28.250 --> 05:32.085
Sound wave is quite competent
at surveillance,

05:32.087 --> 05:33.654
I can assure you.

05:33.656 --> 05:36.957
The fact is, Starscream,
despite your treachery,

05:36.959 --> 05:39.693
I've allowed you to carry on
this long

05:39.695 --> 05:42.062
because I took
a certain delight

05:42.064 --> 05:44.731
in following your string
of failures.

05:44.733 --> 05:47.534
But you've finally
become tiresome,

05:47.536 --> 05:48.602
predictable.

05:48.604 --> 05:51.638
You've hit rock bottom.

05:51.640 --> 05:52.773
[ Whimpering ]

05:52.775 --> 05:54.574
Master, please!

05:54.576 --> 05:59.680
Give me one more chance!
I beg of you!

06:06.954 --> 06:11.558
You have ceased to be of use
to me, Starscream.

06:11.560 --> 06:14.861
So you shall simply
cease to be.

06:14.863 --> 06:17.898
[ Whimpering ]

06:25.473 --> 06:28.575
[ Growls ]

06:32.780 --> 06:34.581
Stay down!

06:45.159 --> 06:47.160
Haaah!

06:47.162 --> 06:51.465
Starscream,
you dare abandon me?!

06:51.467 --> 06:53.100
[ Grunts ]

07:22.230 --> 07:23.930
Scrap!

07:36.043 --> 07:37.677
[ Groans ]

07:43.251 --> 07:44.584
[ Yelps ]

07:44.586 --> 07:46.253
[ Grunting ]

07:46.255 --> 07:47.988
[ Groans ]

08:03.504 --> 08:05.105
What?

08:05.107 --> 08:07.674
[ Echoing ] No!

08:37.378 --> 08:39.044
[ Grunting ]

08:39.047 --> 08:40.947
[ Coughing ]

08:45.753 --> 08:48.088
[ Echoing ] Arcee?

08:48.090 --> 08:50.991
Arcee!

08:53.361 --> 08:54.728
Oh, scrap.

08:59.867 --> 09:01.568
[ Coughing ]

09:03.804 --> 09:05.872
Did <i>i</i> do that?

09:05.874 --> 09:08.008
Don't think so.

09:08.010 --> 09:09.843
Are you okay?

09:09.845 --> 09:13.113
Natch.
What about you?

09:14.448 --> 09:16.316
Peachy.

09:16.318 --> 09:17.984
[ Creaking ]

09:23.257 --> 09:24.424
Whoa!

09:24.426 --> 09:27.627
Don't worry, Miko.
I got it under control.

09:27.629 --> 09:29.562
What do you think
caused the cave-in?

09:29.564 --> 09:30.864
[ Sighs ] Who knows?

09:30.866 --> 09:33.199
I just hope Arcee and Jack
are safe,

09:33.201 --> 09:35.802
'cause we could
definitely use an assist.

09:35.804 --> 09:37.704
Just keep raising
that roof, Bulk.

09:37.706 --> 09:38.972
I'll get us out of here.

09:41.142 --> 09:43.476
[ Grunting ]

09:57.692 --> 10:00.794
[ Grunting ]

10:00.796 --> 10:03.430
[ Coughing ]

10:06.400 --> 10:08.501
[ Laughs evilly ]

10:08.503 --> 10:10.737
Predictable, master?

10:10.739 --> 10:13.340
Is that what you called me?

10:13.342 --> 10:16.810
Well, now who has hit
rock bottom?

10:16.812 --> 10:18.111
What's that?

10:18.113 --> 10:22.349
I'm sorry... I can't hear you
beneath all that rubble!

10:22.351 --> 10:24.484
[ Laughs evilly ]

10:24.486 --> 10:27.654
Farewell, lord Megatron.

10:27.656 --> 10:31.558
May you rest in peace.

10:33.694 --> 10:35.829
But you <i>have</i> survived far worse.

10:35.831 --> 10:37.964
If you managed to free yourself,

10:37.966 --> 10:40.667
you would blame me
for your setback,

10:40.669 --> 10:43.503
and there is nowhere
that I could possibly escape

10:43.505 --> 10:45.205
from your wrath.

10:45.207 --> 10:46.573
Or, worse yet,

10:46.575 --> 10:49.509
your mindless followers
will come looking for you

10:49.511 --> 10:52.012
and take credit
for your rescue...

10:52.014 --> 10:54.647
Credit that could
rightfully be mine.

10:54.649 --> 10:56.249
Raaaah!

10:56.251 --> 10:58.451
Megatron!

11:01.255 --> 11:04.290
[ Panting ]

11:04.292 --> 11:07.127
[ Echoing ] Arcee?

11:07.129 --> 11:09.329
Bulkhead?

11:09.331 --> 11:12.565
Miko!

11:16.637 --> 11:18.338
[ Thud in distance ] Huh?

11:20.041 --> 11:22.709
Well, <i>that</i> could come in handy.

11:28.549 --> 11:31.684
[ Grunting ]

11:35.990 --> 11:37.690
Miko!

11:37.692 --> 11:41.928
[ Sighs ] I'm feeling strong!
[ Sighs ]

11:41.930 --> 11:43.196
No, you're not.

11:43.198 --> 11:45.732
I just need to [Groans]

11:45.734 --> 11:48.802
Rest for a second, that's all.

11:48.804 --> 11:51.171
[ Groans ]

11:51.173 --> 11:54.574
Miko, listen to me.
There's no fresh air down here.

11:54.576 --> 11:57.143
If you use up the oxygen
too fast...

11:57.145 --> 11:58.878
We could suffocate!

11:58.880 --> 12:02.148
Not "we," Miko...
You.

12:02.150 --> 12:04.818
Autobots don't need
to breathe, remember?

12:04.820 --> 12:08.154
Right.
Smack-down in outer space.

12:08.156 --> 12:09.489
[ Chuckles ] That was cool.

12:09.491 --> 12:11.925
[ Groans ] Okay.

12:11.927 --> 12:16.729
What if I just slowed down,
breathed...less...

12:16.731 --> 12:18.498
[ Panting ]

12:21.469 --> 12:25.605
[ Grunting ]

12:25.607 --> 12:28.274
No.
You need to stop... now.

12:28.276 --> 12:30.777
I can't, Bulk.

12:30.779 --> 12:33.613
I have to get you out of here.

12:33.615 --> 12:36.916
[ Grunts ]

12:36.918 --> 12:38.718
[ Sighs ]

12:38.720 --> 12:41.421
Miko, please.
Don't worry about me.

12:41.423 --> 12:43.289
[ Rock settling,
metal creaking ]

12:43.291 --> 12:45.558
[ Straining ] I'm fine.

13:08.349 --> 13:10.817
Roll out.

13:10.819 --> 13:13.052
[ Groaning ]

13:13.054 --> 13:14.621
[ Drilling in distance ]

13:14.623 --> 13:15.822
Do you hear that?

13:15.824 --> 13:17.657
Sounds like...

13:17.659 --> 13:18.758
Drilling.

13:18.760 --> 13:20.493
Got to be Arcee and Jack.

13:20.495 --> 13:23.730
We're in...Here!

13:23.732 --> 13:25.932
[ Straining ] Here!

13:25.934 --> 13:28.601
Miko, grab something,
and bang it on my foot.

13:28.603 --> 13:29.669
Can you do that?

13:34.041 --> 13:36.109
[ Grunting ]

13:40.548 --> 13:42.482
I don't want to hurt you.

13:42.484 --> 13:45.985
I know it's hard to believe,
but I'm tougher than I look.

13:45.987 --> 13:47.287
Now give it all you got.

13:48.722 --> 13:52.392
[ Thudding ]

14:05.005 --> 14:08.208
I suppose helping
those less fortunate

14:08.210 --> 14:11.544
would be completely
out of the question.

14:13.581 --> 14:15.415
If it is the case,

14:15.417 --> 14:18.384
you might as well use your drill
to finish me.

14:18.386 --> 14:22.822
I guarantee you will never have
a better opportunity

14:22.824 --> 14:25.291
than right <i>now.</i>

14:28.128 --> 14:30.563
Well?
What are you waiting for?

14:30.565 --> 14:32.332
Think of the glory.

14:32.334 --> 14:34.200
Seize the day.

14:34.202 --> 14:35.602
Optimus would.

14:35.604 --> 14:39.239
No, he wouldn't.
Not like this.

14:40.975 --> 14:43.309
I will be sure
to share the details

14:43.311 --> 14:46.012
of our little conversation
with Optimus...

14:46.014 --> 14:47.981
The day I rip out his spark!

14:54.888 --> 14:56.889
[ Grunts ]

14:58.459 --> 15:02.061
[ Grunting ]

15:02.063 --> 15:04.464
Thatagirl.

15:07.568 --> 15:08.801
[ Metal groaning ]

15:08.803 --> 15:10.003
What was that?

15:10.005 --> 15:13.039
Nothing. Go on.
Keep banging.

15:13.041 --> 15:14.374
[ Thud ]

15:14.376 --> 15:15.842
[ Grunts ]

15:18.746 --> 15:21.581
Bulkhead, what's happening?
Tell me!

15:21.583 --> 15:26.552
My arms...
They're starting to give.

15:34.121 --> 15:37.590
[ Grunting ]

15:37.592 --> 15:38.925
Does it hurt?

15:38.927 --> 15:41.494
[ Grunts ] A little.

15:43.731 --> 15:44.864
Bulkhead!

15:44.866 --> 15:46.032
Help's coming.

15:46.034 --> 15:47.567
We just got to guide them here.

15:47.569 --> 15:48.668
Hit me again.

15:49.737 --> 15:51.538
Miko, do it!

15:54.341 --> 15:56.376
[ Grunting ]

16:00.181 --> 16:01.648
[ Whimpering ]

16:01.650 --> 16:03.383
[ Drilling in distance ]

16:04.785 --> 16:06.720
Are they any closer?

16:06.722 --> 16:08.154
I can't tell.

16:08.156 --> 16:10.824
The sound is all... unh!...

16:10.826 --> 16:12.926
Freaky in here.

16:12.928 --> 16:14.527
[ Thudding ]

16:14.529 --> 16:15.628
[ Gasps ]

16:18.532 --> 16:20.433
[ Laughs ]

16:20.435 --> 16:21.634
Yes!

16:21.636 --> 16:23.970
Arcee found us!

16:25.706 --> 16:28.241
[ Laughs evilly ]

16:28.243 --> 16:32.078
Put any doubt of my allegiance
to rest.

16:33.781 --> 16:35.715
What's <i>he</i> doing down here?

16:35.717 --> 16:38.651
Miko, get behind me... now!

16:43.524 --> 16:48.762
Well, well, if isn't Bulkhead
and his pet Vermin.

16:48.764 --> 16:54.134
My, you do have your hands full,
don't you, Autobot?

16:54.136 --> 16:56.703
Do whatever you want to me,
Starscream,

16:56.705 --> 16:58.138
but let the human go!

16:58.140 --> 16:59.339
No! [ Strains ]

16:59.341 --> 17:01.441
I'm not leaving you!

17:01.443 --> 17:06.311
It appears that the human
wishes to remain.

17:06.314 --> 17:09.449
Starscream, don't push me!

17:09.451 --> 17:12.551
You like playing
with the big robots,

17:12.554 --> 17:14.454
don't you, little girl?

17:14.455 --> 17:16.723
[ Panting ]

17:19.460 --> 17:20.492
Aah!

17:20.494 --> 17:21.895
[ Chuckling evilly ]

17:27.034 --> 17:28.434
[ Straining ]

17:30.671 --> 17:33.640
[ Growling ]

17:33.642 --> 17:35.875
That's it, Autobot...
I will...

17:35.877 --> 17:37.577
What?

17:37.579 --> 17:38.878
You'll what?

17:38.880 --> 17:41.714
Make me bring down the ceiling
on top of all of us?

17:41.716 --> 17:43.082
Run, Miko!

17:46.320 --> 17:48.354
Yes. Run, Miko.

17:48.356 --> 17:51.324
I would love to see you try.

17:51.326 --> 17:54.394
Really, I would.

17:54.396 --> 17:55.829
[ Thud ]

17:57.598 --> 17:59.365
Aah!

18:03.204 --> 18:06.639
Jack, get Miko
out of here... now!

18:06.641 --> 18:07.907
[ Grunts ]

18:12.012 --> 18:15.014
Come on! Come on!

18:15.016 --> 18:16.349
Run, Miko!

18:23.824 --> 18:26.759
[ Crying ]
We can't leave Bulkhead!

18:26.761 --> 18:28.294
[ Moans ]

18:39.039 --> 18:42.609
And then there were two.

18:45.913 --> 18:48.081
Arcee will save him, won't she?

18:48.083 --> 18:51.050
You and I just need to find
a way out of here

18:51.052 --> 18:53.386
before Megatron
digs himself free.

18:53.388 --> 18:55.622
Megatron's here, too?!

19:00.027 --> 19:01.194
[ Gasps ]

19:01.196 --> 19:03.229
[ Gasps ]

19:03.231 --> 19:05.064
[ Chuckling ]

19:05.066 --> 19:09.035
If you think I'm gonna beg
for mercy, Starscream,

19:09.037 --> 19:10.303
forget it.

19:10.305 --> 19:14.607
Yes, begging for mercy
would be quite pathetic,

19:14.609 --> 19:15.909
wouldn't it?

19:15.911 --> 19:19.345
Well, you're much more valuable
to me alive.

19:19.347 --> 19:21.915
Imagine Megatron's appreciation

19:21.917 --> 19:25.718
when I not only rescue him
but deliver an Autobot.

19:25.720 --> 19:30.924
I believe that would restore
my stature quite nicely.

19:30.926 --> 19:33.426
[ Weapon charges ]

19:35.963 --> 19:39.565
<i>Don't</i> move, Starscream.

19:40.734 --> 19:42.168
Hey, Bulk.

19:42.170 --> 19:43.903
Hey, 'cee.

19:43.905 --> 19:45.271
Raise your hands.

19:45.273 --> 19:47.607
[ Shuddering ]

19:47.609 --> 19:49.976
Aww.

20:03.824 --> 20:06.759
We could finish them
here and now.

20:06.761 --> 20:09.762
Shame we didn't bring
any grenades.

20:09.764 --> 20:12.932
Would Optimus...
finish them?

20:12.934 --> 20:16.169
No.
He probably wouldn't.

20:16.171 --> 20:17.704
Not like this.

20:17.706 --> 20:21.274
But Optimus wouldn't rescue
them, either, right?

20:21.276 --> 20:23.576
Let's go home.

20:28.916 --> 20:32.251
[ Sighs ]

20:34.788 --> 20:38.391
[ Straining ]

20:45.933 --> 20:47.433
[ Gasps ]

20:49.603 --> 20:51.771
Master!

20:51.773 --> 20:53.473
You're alive!

20:53.475 --> 20:55.775
Thank the all spark!

20:58.846 --> 21:02.749
I...I did not abandon you,
master.

21:02.751 --> 21:06.619
I returned...
to save you!

21:06.621 --> 21:08.621
Save me?

21:10.657 --> 21:14.027
Look into my spark,
lord Megatron.

21:14.029 --> 21:16.729
My intentions were true.

21:16.731 --> 21:19.032
Please!

21:19.034 --> 21:21.968
Have mercy!

